==Demographics==
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Sattley had a population of 44. The population density was {{convert|21.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Sattley was 39 (89%) [[White Americans|White]], and 5 (11%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 2 persons (5%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Sattley CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0670336 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 3, 2025}}</ref>

There were 27 households, and the average household size was 1.63.<ref name=DP1/>

The age distribution was 8 people (18%) under the age of 18, 7 people (16%) aged 18 to 24, 8 people (18%) aged 25 to 44, 13 people (30%) aged 45 to 64, and 8 people (18%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 39.0{{nbsp}}years. There were 18 males and 26 females.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 30 housing units at an average density of {{convert|14.7|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 27 (90%) were occupied. Of these, 13 (48%) were owner-occupied, and 14 (52%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

